                "section": "Acquisition",
                "excerpt": "This mod can be purchased unranked from Baro Ki'Teer for 2,995 2,995 and 1,000,000 Credits 1,000,000 . Note however that Baro Ki'Teer's stock changes with each appearance, and may not have this item available every time."
              }
            }
          ],
          "mechanicsEvidence": {
            "status": "draft",
            "notes": [
              {
                "reviewStatus": "draft",
                "provenance": {
                  "pageTitle": "Primed Chamber",
                  "pageId": 101619,
                  "revisionId": 2792156,
                  "section": "Notes",
                  "excerpt": "Despite its name, Primed Chamber is not related to Primed Mods , and was in fact added to the game long before the first such mod. As a result, it is not the \"Primed version\" of Charged Chamber , and thus can be equipped alongside it."
                }
              },
              {
                "reviewStatus": "draft",
                "provenance": {
                  "pageTitle": "Primed Chamber",
                  "pageId": 101619,
                  "revisionId": 2792156,
                  "section": "Notes",
                  "excerpt": "Primed Chamber is applied multiplicatively after all other modifiers from mods and abilities."
                }
              },
              {
                "reviewStatus": "draft",
                "provenance": {
                  "pageTitle": "Primed Chamber",
                  "pageId": 101619,
                  "revisionId": 2792156,
                  "section": "Notes",
                  "excerpt": "For example, a Vectis with a max rank Primed Chamber, Serration , Cryo Rounds , Target Acquired , and Bane of Grineer , and a subsumed Eclipse with base Ability Strength, will deal 225 × (1 + 1.0) × (1 + 1.65) × (1 + 0.90) × (1 + 0.60) × (1 + 0.30) × (1 + 0.30) = 6,127 headshot damage."
                }
              },
              {
                "reviewStatus": "draft",
                "provenance": {
                  "pageTitle": "Primed Chamber",
                  "pageId": 101619,
                  "revisionId": 2792156,
                  "section": "Notes",
                  "excerpt": "The damage bonus applies to all Multishot hits and to Status Damage ."
                }
              },
              {
                "reviewStatus": "draft",
                "provenance": {
                  "pageTitle": "Primed Chamber",
                  "pageId": 101619,
                  "revisionId": 2792156,
                  "section": "Notes",
                  "excerpt": "Stacks additively with Charged Chamber for up to 140% bonus damage."
                }
              },
              {
                "reviewStatus": "draft",
                "provenance": {
                  "pageTitle": "Primed Chamber",
                  "pageId": 101619,
                  "revisionId": 2792156,
                  "section": "Notes",
                  "excerpt": "If used with Ammo Efficiency bonuses, Primed Chamber will provide bonus damage to a shot as long as the magazine counter is at Max Magazine − 1 after a shot is fired."
                }
              },
              {
                "reviewStatus": "draft",
                "provenance": {
                  "pageTitle": "Primed Chamber",
                  "pageId": 101619,
                  "revisionId": 2792156,
                  "section": "Notes",
                  "excerpt": "For example, a Vulkar with Energized Munitions will have the 4th, 5th, 6th, and 7th shots buffed by Primed Chamber, since the magazine counter is at 6 - 1 = 5 during those shots."
                }
              },
              {
                "reviewStatus": "draft",
                "provenance": {
                  "pageTitle": "Primed Chamber",
                  "pageId": 101619,
                  "revisionId": 2792156,
                  "section": "Notes",
                  "excerpt": "Wait to trigger any 100% ammo efficiency effects until a single shot has been consumed from the magazine, since the buff doesn't apply if the mag remains completely full after the shot."
                }
              }
            ],
